{"source_key":"sha256-a74ceb5e1c9633ab993c14c11d587d71","record_index":393,"record_hash":"sha256:5ba0d837031cb9c2dc3300fda7573ca9fb993f7ffe30eb02fcd0eeca742ae30f","timestamp":"2026-05-20T19:28:33.653Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Findings:\\n\\n- [P1] `--limit` is applied too late. [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:167) calls `find_related_sessions`, then truncates at [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:169), but by then [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:240) has already built every rich outline. That means all matched sessions can read turn details and scan transcripts before `--limit 1` takes effect. Fix: pass `limit` into the read layer; resolve `SessionListEntry`, sort by `sort_updated_at`, truncate, then call `related_session_outline`.\\n\\n- [P1] Targeted `sessions` leaks session-wide targets/previews, not just related-turn evidence. [session_outline.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/session_outline.rs:87) loops over every turn summary and [session_outline.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/session_outline.rs:90) aggregates all observed targets; previews also scan the full session transcript at [session_outline.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/session_outline.rs:96). Slice 1 says observed targets should be “seen in the related turns”; this can expose unrelated branch/review/change keys and unrelated later messages. Fix: keep counts/latest activity session-wide if wanted, but build observed targets and previews from `related_turn_keys` only, or rename fields clearly to `session_observed_targets` / `latest_session_preview`.\\n\\n- [P2] Preview generation parses the whole transcript even though it only needs latest user/assistant snippets. [session_outline.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/session_outline.rs:275) walks every entry and [session_outline.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/session_outline.rs:276) parses each JSON record. Fix: scan from newest to oldest and stop once both previews are found; if order is not guaranteed, use `ListEntry.timestamp` to pick the newest matching user/assistant without retaining full records.\\n\\n- [P2] `RecordPreview` exposes `record_hash` in the broad discovery surface. [session_outline.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/session_outline.rs:61) includes it and [session_outline.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/session_outline.rs:293) returns it. That hash is derived from the raw provider record before redaction, so it’s a stable fingerprint of content that may have been redacted in text. Fix: drop `record_hash` from `sessions` previews; `turn_key`, role, timestamp, and text are enough for orientation.\\n\\nNo storage-write changes found in this Slice 1 diff.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T19:28:33.653Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}